The paper discusses the design of a new system for data analysis that brings together ideas from the database, compiler, and programming languages communities. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including cs.DB (Databases), cs.PL (Programming Languages), and cs.SE (Software Engineering). Additionally, the paper proposes novel techniques for achieving maximum performance on a case-by-case basis, which could fall under the sub-categories of cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
